Get raw data

get_raw_data.Rd

A function, that returns all, unprocessed data concerning one of the offices in Warsaw.

get_raw_data(office_name)

Arguments

office_name

character acronym of office in Warsaw.

You can get a list of possible values using get_available_offices function.

Value

A data.frame with following columns:

  • status - either 0 (queue is not operating) or 1 (queue is operating).

  • czasObslugi - expected time of waiting in queue, in minutes. See also: get_waiting_time.

  • lp - ordinal number.

  • idGrupy - ID of a queue from nazwaGrupy.

  • liczbaCzynnychStan - amount of opened counters. See also: get_open_counters.

  • nazwaGrupy - a name of a queue. See also: get_available_queues.

  • literaGrupy - a single letter symbolizing a queue name from nazwaGrupy.

  • liczbaKlwKolejce - amount of people in queue. See also: get_number_of_people.

  • aktualnyNumer - current ticket number. See also: get_current_ticket_number.

See also

get_waiting_time and others to extract data directly.

get_waiting_time_verbose and others for a more verbose output.

Examples

office <- get_available_offices()[1]
get_raw_data(office)
